HAPPY FIRST DAY BACK STUDENTS! We hope your first day back in person went well with your wonderful teachers!

We want to thank all our CBS families for your patience, uplifting words and support in helping us start off this school year in the right direction. We love and appreciate you!üòÅ

*We would like to thank the Gabbitas family for the sweet, positive "Welcome Back" sign! It brightened our morning with big smiles on this first day back in person! Thank you!

*We also would like to thank our parent volunteers who have been so kind enough to bring us lunches throughout this week. The teachers and staff can't thank you enough for your thoughtfulness.

post_text:
Thank you, parents and students, for giving items to share with our soldiers. We were able to collect 3 boxes of hygiene items for Packages for Hope that benefits veterans in transition here in the Valley of the Sun. We collected 3 boxes for Bones from Home that benefits dogs in military service. We collected 8 boxes of treats, personal items, and recreational goods for the soldiers overseas to send them packages from home. The student council delivered them to KMLE radio station where they will package them and send them to our soldiers. THANK YOU!!! ‚ù§
#ChallengerBasicSchool #StudentCouncil #KMLE #PackagesForHope #CommunityService #Gilbert

post_text:
Girls On The Run is coming to Challenger Basic School! Go to www.gotrmc.org to register your girl (3-5th grades only). Registration fees increase after the month of November, so register TODAY! The cost is $180.00 per girl. (This includes their end of season 5k race registration.) Financial scholarships are available allowing any girl the opportunity to participate.

Text/Call Jill Genet (our site Head Coach) for more information. 480-797-2367

Girls on The Run is an after-school program that teaches girls important life lessons such as self-esteem, friendship, communication, and also includes a community service project. These lessons are then reinforced by running combining the mental, emotional, and physical aspects that all must come together to support a young girl's self-esteem. The girls will then complete a 5k in downtown Phoenix on May 4th, 2019, with their Running Buddy (a family member or friend). This program is awesome and well worth the time and investment! The coaches look forward to working with your daughter this season!
